INSERT INTO `sn_news` VALUES ('2', '/upload/news/20180814\\153758926c766c2c7315a58689dae6f9.jpg', '区块链技术可能是避免下一场世界级金融危机的一把钥匙', 'Block chain technology may be a key to avoid the next world financial crisis', '<p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">7月22日，前摩根大通北美投行部副总裁、亚洲区块链学会荣誉学术顾问庞华栋在接受中国经济时报记者采访时表示，“当下，区块链确实存在一些问题，但是不要轻易下结论，要从投资者、行业观察者和实业界等多角度深度解析区块链所带来的问题。”</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">庞华栋表示，</span>“2007年6月，我从麻省理工学院（MIT）毕业后，从业于摩根大通固定收益自营部，当时13个人管理摩根大通400多亿美元，2008年金融危机最惨烈的时候，平均每天亏损3亿美元。日后才渐渐地明白，区块链技术可能是避免下一场世界级金融危机的一把钥匙。”</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">庞华栋继续说，很多中介机构都在应用区块链技术，这将过去不公开和不透明的运作机制，逐渐对利益相关人开放透明，转换成白盒的运作机制，实际上就大大降低了信任成本，反而对机构运作更加有利了，像这种区块链技术的场景应用自然会降低金融风险。</span>“区块链本质上是一种可以去中介或者弱中介化的技术，所以，区块链技术可以用最低的成本去构建信任机制。”</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">据了解，区块链技术被称之为分布式账本技术，是一种互联网数据库技术，其特点是去中心化、公开透明，让每个人均可参与数据库记录。</span></span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">近日，中国银监会首席顾问沈联涛刊文提醒，一旦监管机构开始对</span>ICO和虚拟货币运营发布禁令或进行监管，就会发现其中存在欺诈、损失和操纵行为，最终只能以悲剧收场。对区块链的信任需要通过自身来争取，而不是通过炒作来创造。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">关于区块链发展的未来，庞华栋分析，</span>“现在国内区块链技术的发展阶段属于很早期的阶段，虽然经历了一些比较大的波动，但是发展前景不可限量。”</span></p><p><br/></p>', '<p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">On July 22, Pang Huadong, a former vice president of investment banking at JPMorgan Chase in North America and honorary academic adviser to the Asia Block Chain Society, told the China Economic Times: &quot;At the moment, there are indeed some problems in the block chain, but don&#39;t jump to conclusions. We need to understand them from the perspectives of investors, industry observers and industry. Analyze the problems brought by block chain.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&quot;After graduating from MIT in June 2007, I worked in the fixed income self-management Department of JPMorgan Chase, where 13 people managed JPMorgan Chase for more than $40 billion, and lost an average of $300 million a day at the height of the financial crisis in 2008,&quot; Pang said. It will become clear later that block chain technology may be a key to averting the next world-class financial crisis.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">Pang Huadong continued that many intermediaries are using block chain technology, which will gradually open up and transparent to stakeholders in the past and translate it into a white-box operation mechanism. In fact, it will greatly reduce the cost of trust, but it will be more beneficial to the operation of institutions, such as block chain technology. The application of scenarios will naturally reduce financial risks. &quot;Block chains are essentially a technology that can be de-intermediated or weakly intermediated, so block chains can be used to build trust mechanisms at the lowest cost.&quot;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">It is understood that the block chain technology is called distributed book technology, is an Internet database technology, its characteristics are decentralized, open and transparent, so that everyone can participate in database records.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">Shen Liantao, chief adviser to the China Banking Regulatory Commission (CBRC), warned in a recent paper that once the regulators began to issue bans or supervise ICO and virtual currency operations, fraud, losses and manipulation would be found and could only end in tragedy. Trust in the block chain needs to be fought by itself rather than by speculation.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">About the future of block chain development, Pang Huadong analysis, &quot;Now the development stage of block chain technology in China belongs to a very early stage, although experienced some relatively large fluctuations, but the development prospects are unlimited.&quot;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p><br/></p>', '1534208880', '1535421135', '17');
INSERT INTO `sn_news` VALUES ('3', '/upload/news/20180814\\af4a15ac972cc4cdda6295edb0db7044.jpg', '金融委会议公告罕见盘中发布 强调金融风险进入易发多发期 ！传递了哪些信号？', 'The announcement of the finance committee meeting is rare, and it emphasizes that financial risks will enter the prone period. What signals are transmitted?', '<p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">近日，国务院金融稳定发展委员会召开了第二次会议，进一步明确了未来宏观政策的基调。</span></span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">时隔一月金融委第二次会议召开，与年中政治局会议间隔不到一周。从公告本身内容看，金融委会议是对周一政治局年中会议所确立的政策基调的全面落实。</span></span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">值得注意的是，本次会议未提</span>“去杠杆”，同时突出强调了金融风险。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;line-height:27px\"><span style=\";font-family:黑体;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:黑体\">会议认为，长期积累的金融风险进入易发多发期，外部不确定因素有所增多，需要积极稳妥和更加精准地加以应对。特别值得重视的是，在流动性总量保持合理充裕的条件下，面对实体经济融资难、融资贵的问题，必须更加重视打通货币政策传导机制。</span></span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><strong><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-weight:bold;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">金融风险进入易发多发期</span></span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">会议指出，我国经济尚处于新旧动能转换时期，长期积累的金融风险进入易发多发期，外部不确定因素有所增多，需要积极稳妥和更加精准地加以应对。</span></span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">此前中共中央政治局会议首次提出</span>“六稳”，即稳就业、稳金融、稳外贸、稳外资、稳投资、稳预期。其中“稳金融”就包括了打好防范化解重大风险攻坚战。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">财政部党组书记、部长刘昆日前也在媒体撰文强调，打好防范化解重大风险攻坚战，重点是防控金融风险。</span></span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">综合专家观点，未来我国经济中或存在五方面风险：</span></span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><strong><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-weight:bold;font-size:14px\">1、地方政府债务风险。</span></strong><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">这关系到地方财政稳健运行和实体经济健康发展，以及金融市场稳定和经济社会发展大局。</span></span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><strong><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-weight:bold;font-size:14px\">2、信用收缩。</span></strong><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">信用收缩加剧了经济下行压力，基建投资同比增速持续下滑，房地产投资同比增速开始下降，反弹的制造业同比增速也可能无法延续。</span></span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><strong><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-weight:bold;font-size:14px\">3、房地产市场风险。</span></strong><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">房地产市场风险不仅挤出了实体经济的资源，而且一旦房地产价格泡沫破裂，将引发严重的经济金融危机。</span></span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><strong><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-weight:bold;font-size:14px\">4、地方政府和国有企业去杠杆。</span></strong><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">以资产负债率衡量，去杠杆一方面要求企业利润稳定增长，进而实现资产的保值增值；另一方面要求控制债务增长，从而实现资产负债率逐步下降。</span></span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><strong><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-weight:bold;font-size:14px\">5、互联网金融风险。</span></strong><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">互联网金融当下风控比较薄弱，导致了违约、卷款潜逃、非法集资等。</span></span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">值得注意的是，监管层已经出台了很多金融防风险的相关举措，我国金融风险防控事实上已成效初显。展望未来，仍需精准施策，维护我国金融稳定，打好防范化解重大风险攻坚战。</span></span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><strong><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-weight:bold;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">强调</span>“形成最终需求”稳增长</span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">此次会议强调，在坚持推进供给侧结构性改革的前提下，注意支持形成最终需求，为实体经济创造新的动力和方向。</span></span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">对于</span>“最终需求”的理解，业内专家认为，最终需求就是内需。扩内需是当前更为迫切的目标，扩内需是为了稳增长。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">7月31日召开的中共中央政治局会议提出，财政政策要在扩大内需和结构调整上发挥更大作用。而此前多家券商的研报也表示，下半年经济稳定增长的关键在于内需。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">有专家指出，</span>7月PMI数据显示内需显著回落，进口指数降至荣枯线以下，同时7月铜、锌等有色金属价格均出现较大幅度下跌，这可能意味着全球总需求的回落，三季度大宗商品价格或面临回调，对进口和企业利润均有抑制作用，这些迹象再次表明扩大内需的迫切性。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><strong><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-weight:bold;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">恒丰银行研究院宏观团队分析，从国内层面看，扩内需将成为下半年经济增长的压舱石。</span></span></strong><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">降低进口关税已于</span>7月1日正式实施，更加积极的财政政策和宽信用导向的货币政策，或将提振下半年的基础设施建设，助力内需向好。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><strong><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-weight:bold;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">国家统计局局长宁吉喆表示，经过近几年的调整，中国经济发展格局发生了重大而深刻的变化，内需成为拉动经济增长的绝对力量。</span></span></strong><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">消费对经济增长的贡献持续提升，去年消费对经济增长的贡献率为</span>58.8%，今年一季度达到77.8%。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><strong><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-weight:bold;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">进一步打通货币政策传导机制</span></span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">会议强调，做好当前金融工作，进一步打通货币政策传导机制，必须重点把握好以下几个方面：</span></span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">1、处理好稳增长与防风险的关系。在坚持推进供给侧结构性改革的前提下，注意支持形成最终需求，为实体经济创造新的动力和方向。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">2、处理好宏观总量与微观信贷的关系。在把握好货币总闸门的前提下，要在信贷考核和内部激励上下更大功夫，增强金融机构服务实体经济特别是小微企业的内生动力。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">3、发挥好财政政策的积极作用，用好国债、减税等政策工具，用好担保机制。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">4、深化金融改革，完善大中小金融机构健康发展的格局。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">5、健全正向激励机制，充分调动金融领域中人的积极性，有成绩的要表扬，知错就改的要鼓励。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">6、持续开展打击非法金融活动和非法金融机构专项行动，依法保护投资者权益，维护金融和社会稳定。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">在此时强调进一步打通货币政策传导机制，专家认为有三方面原因：</span></span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">1、经过近期的政策调整，货币市场流动性状况已有明显改善。当下更为关键的问题，是如何推动市场流动性有效注入实体经济领域。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">2、当下货币政策边际放松，但若基础货币投放出来后，社会融资规模无法提高，基础货币只能堆积在金融市场中，而无法变成实体经济融资的增长，可能会形成流动性的“堰塞湖”。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">3、在流动性合理充裕的情况下，打通货币政策传导机制是提高货币政策有效性的关键。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><strong><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-weight:bold;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">专家建议从四方面疏通政策传导机制</span></span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">事实上，当前金融领域最关键的问题是在于金融体系的资金无法顺畅的进入实体经济。</span></span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">摩根士丹利华鑫证券首席经济学家章俊认为，上半年在去杠杆过程中，货币信贷过紧在一定程度上加剧了实体经济融资难融资贵的问题，因此下半年政策调整方向是修正过紧的货币信贷政策来支持实体经济的合理融资。</span></span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><strong><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-weight:bold;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">新时代证券首席经济学家潘向东认为，疏通货币政策传导机制，可从四方面着手。</span></span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">一是央行可通过调整</span>MPA考核参数，支持银行扩充资本等方式，保障表外融资顺利返回表内。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">二是加快国有企业改革，打破</span>“预算软约束”，坚决处理“僵尸企业”，减少无效资金占用。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">三是可继续通过定向降准、</span>MLF续作、支持商业银行购买信用债等方式，引导资金流向民营企业和中小微企业。同时，也应加快利率市场化进程，给予商业银行合适的风险补偿，这样银行才有动力加大对民营企业和中小微企业的信贷投放。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">四是通过加快利率市场化，发展债券市场，完善利率走廊等方式，逐步向价格型调控机制过度。</span></span></p><p><br/></p>', '<p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">Recently, the State Council&#39;s Financial Stability and Development Committee held its second meeting, further clarifying the tone of future macroeconomic policies.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">The second meeting of the finance committee was held one month later, and it was less than a week away from the Political Bureau meeting in mid year. As far as the content of the announcement is concerned, the Financial Committee meeting is a comprehensive implementation of the policy keynote set by the mid-year meeting of the Politburo on Monday.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">It is worth noting that this conference did not mention &quot;deleveraging&quot; and highlighted financial risks.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;line-height:27px\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-weight:normal;font-size:14px\">The meeting held that the long-term accumulation of financial risks into a prone period, increased external uncertainties, need to be actively, steadily and more precise response. Especially, under the condition that the total liquidity remains reasonable and abundant, facing the problems of difficult financing and expensive financing in real economy, we must pay more attention to breaking through the transmission mechanism of monetary policy.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><strong><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-weight:bold;font-size:14px\">Financial risks enter the prone prone period</span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">The meeting pointed out that China&#39;s economy is still in the period of old and new kinetic energy conversion, long-term accumulation of financial risks into a prone period of frequent occurrence, increased external uncertainties, need to be actively, steadily and more accurately respond.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">Prior to the meeting of the Political Bureau of the CPC Central Committee, the &quot;six stability&quot; was first put forward, that is, stable employment, stable finance, stable foreign trade, stable foreign investment, stable investment, stable expectations. Among them, &quot;stable finance&quot; includes the prevention and elimination of major risks.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">Liu Kun, Secretary of the Party Leadership Group of the Ministry of Finance and Minister of Finance, also wrote in the media recently, stressing that the key point is to prevent and control financial risks.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">From the perspective of comprehensive experts, there are five risks in China&#39;s future economy:</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><strong><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-weight:bold;font-size:14px\">1, local government debt risk.</span></strong><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;This is related to the sound operation of local finance and the healthy development of the real economy, as well as the stability of the financial market and the overall situation of economic and social development.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><strong><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-weight:bold;font-size:14px\">2, credit contraction. Credit</span></strong><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;contraction intensified downward pressure on the economy, infrastructure investment continued to decline year-on-year growth, real estate investment began to decline year-on-year growth, the rebound in the manufacturing sector may not be able to continue year-on-year growth.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><strong><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-weight:bold;font-size:14px\">3, the real estate market risks.</span></strong><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;The real estate market risk not only squeezes out the real economy resources, but also once the real estate price bubble bursts, it will trigger a serious economic and financial crisis.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><strong><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-weight:bold;font-size:14px\">4, local governments and state-owned enterprises are deleveraging</span></strong><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">. Measured by the ratio of assets to liabilities, de-leveraging on the one hand requires the steady growth of corporate profits, thereby achieving the value of assets to maintain and increase; on the other hand, it requires the control of debt growth, thus achieving a gradual decline in the ratio of assets to liabilities.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><strong><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-weight:bold;font-size:14px\">5, Internet financial risks.</span></strong><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;Internet finance is relatively weak at present, resulting in default, absconding, illegal fund-raising and so on.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">It is worth noting that the regulatory authorities have introduced a lot of financial risk prevention measures, China&#39;s financial risk prevention and control in fact has achieved initial results. Looking forward to the future, it is still necessary to take precise measures to maintain China&#39;s financial stability and to take good precautions against major risks.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><strong><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-weight:bold;font-size:14px\">Emphasizing the steady growth of &quot;final demand&quot;</span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">The meeting emphasized that on the premise of pushing forward structural reform on the supply side, attention should be paid to supporting the formation of final demand and creating new momentum and direction for the real economy.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">For the understanding of &quot;ultimate demand&quot;, industry experts believe that the final demand is domestic demand. Expanding domestic demand is a more urgent objective at present, and expanding domestic demand is for steady growth.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">The meeting of the Political Bureau of the CPC Central Committee on July 31 proposed that fiscal policy should play a greater role in expanding domestic demand and restructuring. Previous research reports from several brokerages also said that the key to stable economic growth in the second half of this year is domestic demand.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">Some experts pointed out that the July PMI data showed a significant drop in domestic demand, the import index fell below the ebb and flow line, and the July copper, zinc and other non-ferrous metals prices have fallen substantially, which may mean a drop in global total demand, the third quarter commodity prices or facing a correction, both imports and corporate profits have been restrained. These signs once again show the urgency of expanding domestic demand.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><strong><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-weight:bold;font-size:14px\">According to the macro team analysis of Hengfeng Banking Research Institute, from the domestic level, expanding domestic demand will become the ballast of economic growth in the second half of the year. </span></strong><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">Lowering import tariffs was officially implemented on July 1. A more proactive fiscal policy and a more credit-oriented monetary policy may boost infrastructure construction in the second half of the year to boost domestic demand.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><strong><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-weight:bold;font-size:14px\">Ning Jizhe, Director-General of the State Bureau of Statistics, said that after the adjustment in recent years, China&#39;s economic development pattern has undergone major and profound changes, and domestic demand has become an absolute force to promote economic growth. </span></strong><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">Consumption&#39;s contribution to economic growth continued to rise, with consumption contributing 58.8% to economic growth last year and 77.8% in the first quarter of this year.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><strong><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-weight:bold;font-size:14px\">Further opening up the transmission mechanism of monetary policy</span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">The meeting stressed that in order to do a good job in the current financial work and further open up the monetary policy transmission mechanism, we must focus on the following aspects:</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">1, handle the relationship between steady growth and risk prevention. On the premise of pushing forward the supply-side structural reform, attention should be paid to supporting the formation of final demand and creating new impetus and direction for the real economy.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">2, handle the relationship between macro aggregate and micro credit. On the premise of grasping the monetary gate, we should pay more attention to credit assessment and internal incentives, and enhance the endogenous power of financial institutions to serve the real economy, especially small and micro enterprises.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">3. Give full play to the positive role of fiscal policy, make good use of government bonds, tax cuts and other policy tools, and make good use of the guarantee mechanism.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">4, deepen financial reform and improve the healthy development of large and medium-sized financial institutions.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">5. Perfect the positive incentive mechanism, fully mobilize the enthusiasm of people in the financial field, praise those who have made achievements, and encourage those who have made mistakes to correct them.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">6. Continue to carry out special operations against illegal financial activities and illegal financial institutions, protect the rights and interests of investors in accordance with the law, and maintain financial and social stability.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">At this time, it is emphasized that we should further open up the transmission mechanism of monetary policy. Experts believe that there are three reasons:</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">1, through the recent policy adjustment, the liquidity of money market has improved significantly. The more critical issue now is how to push market liquidity into the real economy.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">2. Current monetary policy marginal relaxation, but if the basic money is released, the scale of social financing can not be improved, the basic money can only accumulate in the financial market, and can not become the growth of real economic financing, may form a &quot;barrier lake&quot; of liquidity.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">3. Under the condition of reasonable and abundant liquidity, the key to improve the effectiveness of monetary policy is to break through the transmission mechanism of monetary policy.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><strong><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-weight:bold;font-size:14px\">Experts suggest dredging policy transmission mechanism from four aspects.</span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">In fact, the most critical problem in the financial sector today is that the money in the financial system does not flow smoothly into the real economy.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">Zhang Jun, chief economist of Morgan Stanley Huaxin Securities, believes that tight monetary credit in the first half of the leverage process, to a certain extent, exacerbated the problem of difficult financing of the real economy, so the direction of policy adjustment in the second half of the year is to revise the tight monetary credit policy to support reasonable financing of the real economy.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><strong><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-weight:bold;font-size:14px\">Pan Xiangdong, chief economist of New Age Securities, believes that there are four ways to smooth the transmission mechanism of monetary policy.</span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">First, the central bank can guarantee the smooth return of off-balance-sheet financing by adjusting MPA assessment parameters and supporting banks to expand capital.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">Second, speed up the reform of state-owned enterprises, break the &quot;soft budget constraint&quot;, resolutely deal with &quot;zombie enterprises&quot; and reduce the occupation of invalid funds.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">Third, we can continue to guide the flow of funds to private enterprises and small and medium-sized enterprises by means of targeted reduction, MLF renewal, and support commercial banks to buy credit bonds. At the same time, we should speed up the process of interest rate marketization, and give commercial banks appropriate risk compensation, so that banks have the power to increase credit to private enterprises and small and medium-sized enterprises.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; text-indent: 28px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">Fourthly, we should speed up the marketization of interest rate, develop bond market and perfect interest rate corridor to gradually transfer to price-based regulation mechanism.</span></p>', '1534211142', '1535421107', '14');
INSERT INTO `sn_news` VALUES ('4', '/upload/news/20180814\\2f716af0f1adb9ebe67db65ba1bebd61.jpg', '中国银行业金融机构本外币资产达260万亿元 同比增7%', 'The foreign currency assets of China\'s banking financial institutions amounted to 260 trillion yuan, up by 7% over the same period last year.', '<p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">中新网</span>8月13日电 据中国银保监会网站消息，近日，中国银行保险监督管理委员会发布2018年二季度银行业主要监管指标数据。数据显示，2018年二季度末，中国银行业金融机构本外币资产260万亿元，同比增长7.0%。银行业金融机构本外币负债240万亿元，同比增长6.6%。银行业资产和负债规模稳步增长。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">具体而言，截至</span>2018年二季度末，中国银行业金融机构本外币资产260万亿元，同比增长7.0%。其中，大型商业银行本外币资产96万亿元，占比37.0%，资产总额同比增长5.8%；股份制商业银行本外币资产46万亿元，占比17.7%，资产总额同比增长4.5%。银行业金融机构本外币负债240万亿元，同比增长6.6%。其中，大型商业银行本外币负债89万亿元，占比37.0%，负债总额同比增长5.4%；股份制商业银行本外币负债43万亿元，占比17.8%，负债总额同比增长4.0%。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">金融服务方面，</span>2018年二季度末，银行业金融机构涉农贷款(不含票据融资)余额32万亿元，同比增长7.3%；用于小微企业的贷款(包括小微型企业贷款、个体工商户贷款和小微企业主贷款)余额32万亿元，同比增长13.1%。用于信用卡消费、保障性安居工程等领域贷款同比增长分别为31.1%和44.4%，比各项贷款平均增速高出19.4和32.6个百分点。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">数据显示，信贷资产质量保持平稳。</span>2018年二季度末，商业银行(法人口径，下同)不良贷款余额1.96万亿元，较上季末增加1829亿元；商业银行不良贷款率1.86%，较上季末上升0.12个百分点。2018年二季度末，商业银行正常贷款余额103.1万亿元，其中正常类贷款余额99.6万亿元，关注类贷款余额3.4万亿元。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">数据显示，利润增长基本稳定。</span>2018年上半年，商业银行累计实现净利润10322亿元，同比增长6.37%，增速较去年同期下降1.55个百分点。商业银行平均资产利润率为1.03%，较上季末下降0.02个百分点；平均资本利润率13.70%，较上季末下降0.30个百分点。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">数据显示，风险抵补能力较为充足。</span>2018年二季度末，商业银行贷款损失准备余额为3.50万亿元，较上季末增加1036亿元；拨备覆盖率为178.70%，较上季末下降12.58个百分点；贷款拨备率为3.33%，较上季末下降0.01个百分点。2018年二季度末，商业银行(不含外国银行分行)核心一级资本充足率为10.65%，较上季末下降0.06个百分点；一级资本充足率为11.20%，较上季末下降0.07个百分点；资本充足率为13.57%，较上季末下降0.07个百分点。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">数据显示，流动性水平保持稳健。</span>2018年二季度末，商业银行流动性比例为52.42%，较上季末上升1.02个百分点；人民币超额备付金率2.19%，较上季末上升0.67个百分点；存贷款比例(人民币境内口径)为72.30%，较上季末上升1.13个百分点。</span></p><p><br/></p>', '<p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">BEIJING, Aug. 13, according to the China Banking and Insurance Regulatory Commission website news, recently, the China Banking and Insurance Regulatory Commission issued the second quarter of 2018 banking regulatory indicators data. Data show that at the end of the second quarter of 2018, domestic and foreign currency assets of China&#39;s banking financial institutions reached 2.6 billion yuan, up 7.0% year-on-year. The foreign currency liabilities of the banking financial institutions amounted to 240 trillion yuan, an increase of 6.6% over the same period last year. The scale of banking assets and liabilities has increased steadily.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">Specifically, by the end of the second quarter of 2018, the domestic and foreign currency assets of China&#39;s banking financial institutions were 2.6 billion yuan, up 7.0% year-on-year. Among them, 96 trillion yuan (37.0%) of domestic and foreign currency assets of large commercial banks, 5.8% of total assets, 46 trillion yuan (17.7%) of joint-stock commercial banks, and 4.5% of total assets. The foreign currency liabilities of the banking financial institutions amounted to 240 trillion yuan, an increase of 6.6% over the same period last year. Among them, the liabilities of large commercial banks in local and foreign currencies are 89 trillion yuan, accounting for 37.0%, the total liabilities are 5.4% higher than that of the previous year; the liabilities of joint-stock commercial banks in local and foreign currencies are 43 trillion yuan, accounting for 17.8%, and the total liabilities are 4.0% higher than that of the previous year.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">In terms of financial services, at the end of the second quarter of 2018, the balance of agricultural-related loans (excluding paper financing) of banking financial institutions was 32 trillion yuan, an increase of 7.3% compared with the same period of the previous year; and the balance of loans for small and micro enterprises (including loans for small and micro enterprises, loans for individual businesses and loans for small and micro entrepreneurs) was 32 trillion yuan, an increase of 13.1%. Loans for credit card consumption and affordable housing projects grew 31.1% and 44.4% year-on-year, 19.4 and 32.6 percentage points higher than the average growth rate of loans.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">Data show that the quality of credit assets remains stable. At the end of the second quarter of 2018, the balance of non-performing loans of commercial banks (legal person caliber, the same below) was 1.96 trillion yuan, an increase of 182.9 billion yuan from the end of the previous quarter; the non-performing loan rate of commercial banks was 1.86%, up 0.12 percentage points from the end of the previous quarter. At the end of the second quarter of 2018, the normal loan balance of commercial banks was 103.1 trillion yuan, of which the normal loan balance was 99.6 trillion yuan and the concerned loan balance was 3.4 trillion yuan.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">Data show that profit growth is basically stable. In the first half of 2018, commercial banks achieved a net profit of 103.22 billion yuan, an increase of 6.37% over the same period of last year, a decrease of 1.55 percentage points over the same period of last year. The average asset profit margin of commercial banks was 1.03%, down 0.02 percentage points from the end of last quarter, and the average capital profit margin was 13.70%, down 0.30 percentage points from the end of last quarter.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">Data show that risk tolerance is more adequate. At the end of the second quarter of 2018, the loan loss reserve balance of commercial banks was 3.50 trillion yuan, an increase of 103.6 billion yuan from the end of the previous quarter; the reserve coverage rate was 178.70%, down 12.58 percentage points from the end of the previous quarter; and the loan reserve rate was 3.33%, down 0.01 percentage points from the end of the previous quarter. At the end of the second quarter of 2018, the core primary capital adequacy rate of commercial banks (excluding foreign bank branches) was 10.65%, down 0.06 percentage points from the end of the previous quarter; the primary capital adequacy rate was 11.20%, down 0.07 percentage points from the end of the previous quarter; and the capital adequacy rate was 13.57%, down 0.07 percentage points from the end of the previous quarter.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">Data show that liquidity levels remain stable. At the end of the second quarter of 2018, the liquidity ratio of commercial banks was 52.42%, up 1.02 percentage points from the end of last quarter; the excess reserve ratio of RMB was 2.19%, up 0.67 percentage points from the end of last quarter; and the deposit-loan ratio (RMB domestic caliber) was 72.30%, up 1.13 percentage points from the end of last quarter.</span></p><p><br/></p>', '1534211855', '1535421081', '6');
INSERT INTO `sn_news` VALUES ('5', '/upload/news/20180814\\a5be8d1bc05e7437ddbc3d05cccf6393.jpg', '金融债券试水弹性招标 发行调整比例不超过50%', 'Financial bond test water flexibility tender offer adjustment ratio not exceeding 50%', '<p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">8月13日，中国债券信息网发布了《中国人民银行金融市场司关于试点开展金融债券弹性招标发行的通知》。所谓弹性招标发行，是指金融机构在银行债券市场招标发行金融债券时，有权根据事先设定的规则，动态调整最终债券发行规模的行为。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">根据该通知，试点阶段，单期金融债券发行规模弹性调整比例不得超过其初始发行规模的</span>50%。试点初期，弹性招标发行暂适用于开发性、政策性金融债券的发行，中国人民银行金融市场司可根据试点情况逐步扩大试点范围。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">在业内人士看来，弹性招标发行意味着金融债可以在市场认购热情较高时扩大发行规模，在市场需求较小时相应减少发行规模，灵活调整最终发行量，有利于金融债券发行机制的进一步完善。</span></span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">今年以来，由于市场风险偏好降低，国债、政策性金融债券等在一级市场较受欢迎，市场需求旺盛。统计显示，上周，国债发行量为</span>1963.20亿元，净融资1403.23亿元。政策性银行债发行量为1371.10亿元，净融资1157.80亿元。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">在承销商选择方面，通知要求，金融债券发行应选择具备金融债券承销经验和能力的机构作为承销商，并根据发行规模合理确定主承销商（如有）数量。此外，金融债券招标触发发行规模弹性调整机制的，发行人应严格按照事先披露的规则进行调整操作。调整结果经发行人和中国人民银行观察员签字确认后方能生效，有关决策材料应妥善保存。</span></span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">在市场化发行方面，通知强调，金融债券发行应坚持市场化原则合理定价，充分体现金融债券的风险收益特征，不得以互持等方式扭曲金融债券定价。对于发行价格与二级市场上市交易价格偏离过大的情况，发行人或主承销商（如有）应在金融债券发行情况报告中予以说明，并有义务接受监管机构、市场机构的质询。</span></span></p><p><br/></p>', '<p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">On August 13, the China Bond Information Network issued the Circular of the Financial Market Department of the People&#39;s Bank of China on the pilot implementation of flexible tender issuance of financial bonds. The so-called flexible tender issuance refers to the financial institutions in the bank bond market tender issuance of financial bonds, have the right to dynamically adjust the final bond issuance scale according to pre-set rules.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">According to the circular, in the pilot phase, the flexible adjustment ratio of the issuance scale of single-issue financial bonds shall not exceed 50% of their initial issuance scale. At the initial stage of the pilot project, flexible tender issuance is temporarily suitable for the issuance of developing and policy-oriented financial bonds. The Financial Market Department of the People&#39;s Bank of China may gradually expand the scope of the pilot project according to the pilot project.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">In the view of the industry, flexible tendering means that the issuing scale of financial bonds can be enlarged when the market is enthusiastic for subscribing, the issuing scale can be reduced correspondingly when the market demand is small, and the final issuing volume can be adjusted flexibly, which is conducive to the further improvement of the issuing mechanism of financial bonds.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">Since this year, as market risk preference has been reduced, national debt, policy-based financial bonds and other popular in the primary market, market demand is strong. Statistics show that last week, the issue amount of treasury bonds was 196 billion 320 million yuan, and net financing was 140 billion 323 million yuan. The issuing amount of policy banks is 137 billion 110 million yuan, and net financing is 115 billion 780 million yuan.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">In terms of underwriter selection, the notice requires that the issuing of financial bonds should select institutions with financial bond underwriting experience and ability as underwriters, and determine the number of principal underwriters (if any) according to the issuing scale. In addition, the issuer should strictly follow the rules of prior disclosure to adjust the elastic adjustment mechanism of issuance scale triggered by financial bond tendering. The result of the adjustment shall not come into effect until it is signed and confirmed by the issuer and the observer of the People&#39;s Bank of China, and the relevant decision-making materials shall be properly preserved.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; text-indent: 28px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">In the aspect of market-oriented issuance, the circular emphasizes that the issuance of financial bonds should adhere to the principle of market-oriented and reasonable pricing, fully embody the risk-return characteristics of financial bonds, and should not distort the pricing of financial bonds by means of interdependence. The issuer or the principal underwriter (if any) shall state in the financial bond issuance report that the issuance price deviates too much from the listed transaction price in the secondary market, and shall be obliged to accept the interrogation of the regulatory authorities and market institutions.</span></p>', '1534212525', '1535421070', '14');
INSERT INTO `sn_news` VALUES ('6', '/upload/news/20180814\\db65ab7ee491c8e842ac7ec1049e54ea.jpg', 'AI+金融，造势宣传背后剩什么？', 'AI+ finance, what\'s left behind the publicity campaign?', '<p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">从去年开始，各行各业刮起了</span>“AI风”，AI+医疗、AI+安防、AI+教育、AI+娱乐、AI+零售，AI+金融自然不会缺席，创新工场董事长兼CEO李开复就曾多次表示，人工智能最好的应用领域之一就是金融业，因为这是唯一纯数字的领域。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">中国银行、建设银行、工商银行、中国平安、国泰君安、华泰证券等都宣布开始涉足金融智能化领域，主打人工智能概念的产品层出不穷。但事实上，无论各金融机构如何宣传造势，人工智能在金融领域的应用都大致归为三类：一类是智能投顾；第二类是智能客服；第三类是金融预测与反欺诈。</span></span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><strong><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-weight:bold;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">智能投顾</span></span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">智能投顾模式诞生于</span>2008年，2011年在美国市场显著加速发展。国外机构来看，Vanguard、Charles Schwab是较早布局智能投顾传统金融机构。目前规模也最大。除此之外，2016年以来，德意志银行、TD Ameritrade、美银美林、高盛等大举进入智能投顾领域。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">截至</span>2016年9月，美国传统资产管理机构通过智能投顾模式管理的资产规模约520亿美元，年均复合增长率179%；同期，美国独立智能投顾公司资管管理规模达到132亿美元，增长率56%。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">国内最先亮出</span>“智能投顾”的金融机构就是招商银行。于2016年年底推出的摩羯智投是针对公募基金的基金组合，其官方介绍中也称，只是“智能基金组合销售服务”。随后，工商银行也推出了智能投顾“AI投”。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">目前的智能投顾绝大多数是风险投资组合。主要面向个体投资者或银行、券商、基金代销机构等需要大量资产配置的巨体量投资主体。其中，智能投顾大类资产配置的核心问题是高效可靠的产品画像，而针对个体终端用户的智能投顾则需要同时解决好产品画像和用户画像两方面问题。无论哪一种，关键性影响因素都是基础数据的量级和准确性以及算法模型的有效性。</span></span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><strong><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-weight:bold;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">智能客服</span></span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">客服领域，传统商业银行或零售银行，很大程度要跟客户打交道，现在很多地方可能被取代，人工智能技术引入专家系统，将</span>80%用户的常见问题进行学习，只需要很少的客服人员就可以通过人工智能识别客户的问题，提供相应的候选解答和金融知识，极大提高效率。人工智能助理、人工智能信贷员、人工智能决策放款收款都存在，还有智能推进系统。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">AI+金融，造势宣传背后剩什么？</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">比如智能客服可以通过对人语音的挖掘判断出对方来电的原因、对方来电的情绪、以及对方的内心诉求，然后将它转交给相应的客服，比说顾客是来投诉的，还是来咨询某种业务的。</span></span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><strong><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-weight:bold;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">金融预测与反欺诈</span></span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">金融的核心就是风险，风险是永远存在的，没有绝对的安全。人的精力和注意力都是有限的，而通过利用机器对数据的大规模以及高频率的处理能力，却可以减少风险，做一个准确的风险评估。如首先是对个人的信贷或者企业的投资的这些判断，然后再通过大量的数据分析每一个投资的环节，然后人工通过最后的一个风险控制来做一个处理。美国一家人工智能公司，专门挖掘个人的隐私信息，但现在利用这项技术来做好事，不去泄露用户的隐私，而是监测整个互联网，当发现有人的隐私泄露的时候，启动报警，这在金融诈骗肆虐的今天是很重要的一项应用。</span></span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">使用</span>AI来识别和判断每一笔支付交易，对其分类和标记；人工智可以识别出的支付欺诈，并且收集客户反馈不断迭代改进更加精确。比如信用卡存在被盗刷的可能，那么人工智能就可以用来判断到底是真的消费记录还是一个欺诈的消费。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><strong><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-weight:bold;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">编辑观点</span></span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; text-indent: 28px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">AI进入金融领域早已不是什么新鲜事了，但是目前“AI+金融”主要是对数据的整理和处理，还有金融的交易决策、风险控制，AI若想掀起金融行业的巨浪还为时尚早。</span></p>', '<p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">Since last year, there has been a &quot;AI wind&quot; in all walks of life. AI + health care, AI + security, AI + education, AI + entertainment, AI + retail, AI + finance will naturally not be absent. Kaifu Lee, chairman and CEO of Innovation Works, has repeatedly said that one of the best areas of application of artificial intelligence is the financial industry, because it is the only area of pure numbers.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">Bank of China, Construction Bank of China, Industrial and Commercial Bank of China, Ping An of China, Guotai Junan, Huatai Securities and so on have announced that they have begun to step into the field of financial intelligence, and the main concepts of artificial intelligence products emerge in endlessly. But in fact, regardless of how financial institutions propaganda momentum, the application of artificial intelligence in the financial field are generally classified into three categories: one is intelligent investment; the second is intelligent customer service; the third is financial forecasting and anti-fraud.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><strong><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-weight:bold;font-size:14px\">Intelligent investment</span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">The intelligent shopping mode was born in 2008 and accelerated significantly in the US market in 2011. Foreign institutions, Vanguard, Charles Schwab is an early layout of intelligent financial institutions to invest in traditional institutions. At present, the scale is also the largest. In addition, since 2016, Deutsche Bank, TD Ameritrade, Bank of America Merrill Lynch, Goldman Sachs and other large-scale into the field of intelligent investment.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">As of September 2016, the assets managed by traditional asset management institutions in the United States were about $52 billion, with an average compound annual growth rate of 179%; during the same period, the assets managed by independent intelligent investment companies in the United States reached $13.2 billion, a growth rate of 56%.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">The first financial institution in China to display &quot;intelligent investment&quot; is China Merchants Bank. The Capricorn Intelligence Investment, launched at the end of 2016, is a portfolio of funds targeted at public funds. It is also officially described as a &quot;smart fund portfolio sales service&quot;. Subsequently, ICBC also launched intelligent investment &quot;AI investment&quot;.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">Most of the current intelligent investors are venture capital portfolios. Mainly for individual investors or banks, securities firms, fund dealers and other large-scale investment entities that need a large number of asset allocation. Among them, the core problem of intelligent portfolio allocation is efficient and reliable product portrait, while intelligent portrait for individual end users needs to solve both product portrait and user portrait problems. Either way, the key factors are the magnitude and accuracy of the underlying data and the effectiveness of the algorithm model.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><strong><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-weight:bold;font-size:14px\">Intelligent customer service</span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">In the field of customer service, traditional commercial banks or retail banks have to deal with customers to a great extent. Now many places may be replaced. Artificial intelligence technology is introduced into expert systems to learn the common problems of 80% of users. Only a small number of customer service personnel can identify customers&#39;problems through artificial intelligence and provide corresponding information. The candidate answers and financial knowledge greatly improve efficiency. Artificial Intelligence Assistants, Artificial Intelligence Credit Officers, Artificial Intelligence Decision Lending Receipts, and Intelligent Propulsion Systems exist.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">AI+ finance, what&#39;s left behind the publicity campaign?</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">For example, smart customer service can identify the reason for each other&#39;s calls, the emotions of each other&#39;s calls, and the inner demands of the other, and then transfer it to the corresponding customer service, such as customers to complain, or to consult a certain business.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><strong><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-weight:bold;font-size:14px\">Financial forecasting and anti fraud</span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">The core of finance is risk. Risk is always there. There is no absolute safety. People&#39;s energy and attention are limited, and by using the large-scale and high-frequency processing power of the machine on the data, it can reduce the risk and make an accurate risk assessment. For example, first of all, these judgments about personal credit or business investment, and then through a large number of data analysis of each investment link, and then manually through the last risk control to do a deal. An artificial intelligence company in the United States, specializing in mining personal privacy information, but now using this technology to do a good job, not to divulge the privacy of users, but to monitor the entire Internet, when found that someone&#39;s privacy leaks, start alarm, which is a very important application in today&#39;s financial fraud rage.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">AI is used to identify and judge each payment transaction, classify and mark it; AI is used to identify payment fraud and collect customer feedback to iterate and improve it more accurately. For example, credit cards may be stolen and swiped, so artificial intelligence can be used to determine whether a real consumer record or a fraudulent consumer.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><strong><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-weight:bold;font-size:14px\">Editorial views</span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; text-indent: 28px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">AI&#39;s entry into the financial sector is not new, but the current &quot;AI + finance&quot; is mainly the collation and processing of data, as well as financial transaction decisions, risk control, if AI wants to set off a huge wave in the financial industry is still too early.</span></p>', '1534213339', '1535421062', '14');
INSERT INTO `sn_news` VALUES ('7', '/upload/news/20180814\\136791a60ee579a473e298d92cc1f3ff.jpeg', '待定', 'undetermined', '<p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">一篇对全球</span>30多名金融专业人士的调查显示，他们大多数认为，美国债券是目前最脆弱的资产。投资大师罗杰斯更是用了十分肯定的语气警告称，在庞大的债务问题重压下，美国面临着比2008年金融海啸还要严重的一场危机，受美国债务及美股高估值的影响，美元资产（美股为代表）或将成为威胁。他表示，下一场金融危机爆发的时间表，市场崩盘来得可能要比大家想象的更快。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">众所周知，上一次金融危机是在</span>2008年9月15日爆发并引发全球经济危机的金融危机，主要起因是美国的房地产泡沫及金融衍生工具的杠杆造成的，最终引发了波及全球的金融危机。2008年9月，雷曼兄弟破产和美林公司被收购标志着金融危机的全面爆发。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">根据资料显示</span>08年债务公司雷曼债务逾6130亿美元！不仅如此，这次危机还造成美国及全球实体经济的衰退，很多貌似强大的国家一夜之间就达到了濒临破产的边缘，正所谓“覆巢之下，焉有完卵！世界巨头的危机靠他们自己是无法消化的，中国虽然没有在金融上遭受严重危机的冲击；</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">但全球金融危机及经济衰退的影响对中国的冲击和考验也是严峻的。例如美国</span>7000亿美金的救市资金肯定不会自己全部买单，当时的中国势必会成为最终的买单一族，只是买单多少的问题而已；并且08年金融危机也是造成中国股市股灾爆发的原因之一。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">所以说金融风暴往往会伴随着大面积的资产价格崩盘，一般股市，债市，汇市，楼市会出现全面溃败的局面，居民财富损失惨重，如果不出面干预，极易引发各国的经济危机，出现社会动荡。</span></span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">而最近，知名趋势预言家、</span>Trends Journal杂志出版商GeraldCelente在其发布的最新一份报告中警告称，全球货币“大溃败”或即将来临，这将在全球市场造成巨大的混乱，这对市场造成的冲击远远大于土耳其市场危机引发的震荡。换句话说，土耳其股债汇市场的大溃败可能只是刚刚开始，Gerald Celente进一步警示，随着主权货币，尤其是一些“三高”经济体（结构性赤字高企、高通胀及高负债）的金融市场出现震荡，这种趋势似乎已经越来越清楚了。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; text-indent: 28px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">更让人害怕的是，目前全球债务已经高达</span>237万亿美元，且其中大部分以美元计价，而美元升值使得许多经济体在本币走弱时更难偿还债务，而一旦出现债务违约，就意味着本币将会更弱了，进而形成一个恶性循环，直到货币“大溃败”的到来。不仅如此，我们发现有一个让市场更敏感的指标也已经触礁至08年金融危机前水平，十年期美国国债期限利差收窄至近十年以来的最低水平，这增加了市场担忧。虽然现在的金融市场不容乐观，但是被誉为最富远见的华尔街金融大鳄吉姆·罗杰斯却说或许还有一种方法可以让你在这次的危机中幸存，接下来“盘姿”会给大家推送出来，代码“001”。</span></p>', '<p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">A survey of more than 30 financial professionals around the world shows that most of them believe that US bonds are the most vulnerable asset at present. Rogers, the investment guru, warned in a very positive tone that under the weight of the huge debt problem, the United States was facing a crisis worse than the 2008 financial tsunami, and that US dollar assets (represented by US stocks) could become a threat because of the high valuation of US debt and stocks. He said the next financial crisis could come sooner than anyone thought.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">As we all know, the last financial crisis broke out on September 15, 2008 and triggered the global economic crisis, mainly due to the U. S. real estate bubble and the leverage of financial derivatives, eventually triggered the global financial crisis. In September 2008, the bankruptcy of Lehman brothers and the acquisition of Merrill Lynch marked the outbreak of the financial crisis.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">According to the data, Lehman debt of the 08 year debt company exceeds US $613 billion. Not only that, but the crisis has also caused a recession in the real economy of the United States and the world, and many seemingly powerful countries are on the verge of bankruptcy overnight, so-called &quot;under the cover of the nest, there is no end! The crisis of the world&#39;s giants can not be digested by themselves, although China has not suffered a serious financial crisis.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">But the impact and test of the global financial crisis and economic recession on China is also grim. For example, the US $700 billion bailout fund will certainly not pay for all of its own, then China will inevitably become the ultimate single buyer, just how much to pay for it; and the 2008 financial crisis is also one of the reasons for the outbreak of China&#39;s stock market disaster.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">Therefore, financial turmoil often accompanied by a large area of asset prices collapse, the general stock market, bond market, foreign exchange market, the property market will be a comprehensive collapse of the situation, the loss of wealth of residents is heavy, if not intervened, it is very easy to trigger economic crises in various countries, social unrest.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">Recently Gerald Celente, a prominent trend predictor and publisher of Trends Journal magazine, warned in his latest report that a global currency &quot;crash&quot; or imminent, would create enormous disruption in the global market, with the impact on the market much greater than the Turkish market crisis caused by the shocks. In other words, the Turkish debt-equity market crash may have just begun, and Gerald Celente further warns that this trend seems increasingly clear as sovereign currencies, especially the financial markets of some &quot;three-high&quot; economies (high structural deficits, high inflation and high debt) shake.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; text-indent: 28px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">Even more frightening is the fact that global debt is now as high as $237 trillion, most of which is denominated in dollars, and the appreciation of the dollar makes it harder for many economies to repay their debts when their currencies weaken. The coming of a great defeat. What&#39;s more, we found that one of the indicators that made the market more sensitive had hit pre-crisis levels in 2008, and the spread on 10-year Treasury bonds had narrowed to its lowest level in nearly a decade, adding to market concerns. While the financial markets are not optimistic, Jim Rogers, the most visionary Wall Street financial crocodile, says there may be another way to survive the crisis, and the &quot;posture&quot; will be pushed out with the code &quot;001&quot;.</span></p>', '1534214001', '1535421039', '22');
INSERT INTO `sn_news` VALUES ('8', '/upload/news/20180814\\ddf74dfefcb0121d6a15a7b8f28c2977.png', '疏通货币政策传导机制丨提升金融服务实体经济能力', 'Dredging monetary policy transmission mechanism to enhance financial services\' real economic capacity', '<p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">近日，国务院金融稳定发展委员会召开第二次会议强调，在流动性总量保持合理充裕的条件下，面对实体经济融资难、融资贵的问题，必须更加重视打通货币政策传导机制，提高服务实体经济的能力和水平。</span></span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">当前，两种看似矛盾的现象同时存在：一方面，市场流动性合理充裕，货币市场利率稳中有降；另一方面，实体经济尤其是小微企业融资难、融资贵问题仍然突出。这对看似矛盾的现象同时出现，关键就在于货币政策传导机制存在梗阻。</span></span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">摸清</span>“堵在哪儿”是疏通货币政策传导机制的关键。中国人民银行货币政策委员会委员、清华大学金融与发展研究中心主任马骏认为，央行将流动性注入银行体系后，受到资金供求双方意愿和能力的制约，信用扩张受到供给端和需求端多重约束，金融体系“有钱”难以用出去，也难以用到最需要的地方。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">一方面，从需求端看，受清理规范地方政府债务、房地产市场调控、环保督查等影响，投向地方政府隐性债务、房地产、环评不达标企业、产能过剩等领域的融资需求显著下降。</span></span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">另一方面，从供给端看，监管趋严、市场风险偏好下降，导致金融机构积极性不强，业务明显收缩。部分金融机构急于清理涉及地方政府的项目，委托贷款、信托贷款到期后难以按原方式续作。</span>“由于金融机构和金融市场风险偏好下降，中小企业、民营企业和环保企业在这一轮调整过程中融资难度明显上升。”马骏表示。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">那么，如何打通梗阻？国家金融与发展实验室副主任曾刚认为，可以从结构性措施着手，提升金融机构向小微企业、民营企业进行信贷投放的意愿。</span></span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">一系列支持小微企业的结构性措施已经出台。</span>6月23日，5部门联合印发《关于进一步深化小微企业金融服务的意见》，以货币政策、财税支持、监管考核等方式，提出了23条小微企业融资的支持措施。为提高金融机构使用支小支农再贷款的积极性，中国人民银行还放宽支小再贷款申请条件、放宽小微企业贷款资产支持证券发行要求等。接下来，金融机构小微企业贷款利息收入还有望免征增值税。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">今年上半年，新增人民币贷款在社会融资规模增量中占比超过</span>96%，创下近十几年来的新高。银行在企业融资中几乎是唯一融资来源。因此，要缓解企业融资难，增加银行信贷额度、提升其积极性是关键。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">多位专家建议，应适度放松对银行的宏观审慎评估</span>(MPA)考核，适度放松可以让银行有更多的表内额度，承接表外资产回表。交通银行首席经济学家连平也指出，为缓解银行表内信贷需求压力，建议适当增加今年银行信贷投放额度，可以相应适度放松MPA考核，同时拓展银行资本补充渠道，如支持银行发行可转债和增发股票等。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">不过，</span>“千军万马挤独木桥”不是长久之计，解决企业融资难、融资贵问题，关键还要拓宽除银行之外的其他融资渠道。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">中国人民银行参事盛松成表示，当前在所有融资渠道中，实体经济基本依靠人民币贷款融资，其他融资工具、融资渠道几乎没有得到有效利用。盛松成认为，要正确理解表外融资与表内融资的关系，在符合监管要求和风险防控的前提下，适当保留表外融资，增加企业尤其是小微企业的融资渠道。</span></span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; text-indent: 28px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">“在‘堵偏门’的同时，也要‘开正门’。”连平认为，要把握和控制好治理整顿信托贷款、委托贷款等“影子融资”的节奏和力度。在“堵偏门”，即对不规范、有潜在风险隐患的非信贷融资开展治理整顿的同时，也要“开正门”，对那些真正能满足实体经济融资需求、规范合理的信托贷款、委托贷款等予以鼓励和支持，促进其平稳增长，发挥对银行信贷融资的补充作用。</span></p>', '<p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">Recently, the State Council&#39;s Financial Stability and Development Committee held its second meeting, stressing that under the condition of reasonable and sufficient liquidity, facing the problem of difficult financing and expensive financing in the real economy, we must pay more attention to the monetary policy transmission mechanism and improve the ability and level of serving the real economy.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">At present, two seemingly contradictory phenomena exist at the same time: on the one hand, the market liquidity is reasonable and abundant, the interest rate in the money market is stable and declining; on the other hand, the real economy, especially small and micro enterprises financing difficulties, financing problems are still prominent. The key to this seemingly contradictory phenomenon lies in the obstruction of the transmission mechanism of monetary policy.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">Finding out where to plug is the key to dredging the transmission mechanism of monetary policy. Ma Jun, member of the Monetary Policy Committee of the People&#39;s Bank of China and director of the Finance and Development Research Center of Tsinghua University, believes that the central bank, after injecting liquidity into the banking system, is constrained by the willingness and ability of both sides of the capital supply and demand, the credit expansion is constrained by multiple constraints on the supply side and the demand side, and the &quot;money&quot; of the financial system is difficult to It is also difficult to use the most needed place.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">On the one hand, from the demand side, affected by the liquidation and standardization of local government debt, real estate market regulation, environmental protection supervision, the demand for financing to local government implicit debt, real estate, environmental impact assessment substandard enterprises, excess capacity and other areas decreased significantly.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">On the other hand, from the supply side, tighter regulation and lower market risk appetite lead to weak enthusiasm of financial institutions and obvious contraction of business. Some financial institutions are eager to clean up projects involving local governments, and it is difficult for them to renew their loans and trust loans after they expire. &quot;SMEs, private enterprises and environmental protection enterprises have become more difficult to finance in this round of adjustment because of the decrease of risk preference of financial institutions and financial markets.&quot; Ma Jun said.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">So how do we get through the obstruction? Zeng Gang, deputy director of the National Laboratory of Finance and Development, believes that structural measures can be taken to enhance the willingness of financial institutions to lend to small and micro enterprises and private enterprises.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">A series of structural measures supporting small and micro enterprises have been introduced. On June 23, the five departments jointly issued the Opinions on Further Deepening the Financial Services of Small and Micro Enterprises, and put forward 23 supporting measures for financing of small and micro enterprises by means of monetary policy, fiscal and taxation support, supervision and assessment. In order to improve the enthusiasm of financial institutions to use small-scale loans to support agriculture, the People&#39;s Bank of China has also relaxed the application conditions for small-scale loans, and relaxed the requirements for issuing asset-backed securities for small and micro enterprises. Next, financial institutions small and micro enterprises loan interest income is also expected to be exempt from value-added tax.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">In the first half of this year, the new Renminbi loans accounted for more than 96% of the increase in the scale of social financing, reaching a new high in the last decade. Banks are almost the only source of financing in corporate finance. Therefore, it is the key to ease the financing difficulties of enterprises, increase bank credit lines and enhance their enthusiasm.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">Several experts suggested that the assessment of macro-prudential assessment (MPA) of banks should be moderately relaxed, and moderately relaxed so that banks can have more on-balance-sheet quotas to accept the return of off-balance-sheet assets. Lian Ping, chief economist of Bank of Communications, also pointed out that in order to alleviate the pressure on bank demand for credit in the balance sheet, it was suggested that the appropriate increase in the amount of bank credit this year could moderately relax the MPA assessment, while expanding bank capital supplementary channels, such as supporting banks to issue convertible bonds and issuing stocks.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">Nevertheless, it is not a long-term solution to the problem of &quot;crowding a single wooden bridge with thousands of troops&quot;. The key is to broaden other financing channels besides banks.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">Sheng Songcheng, a counselor of the People&#39;s Bank of China, said that at present, the real economy basically relies on Renminbi loans in all financing channels, while other financing tools and channels have hardly been effectively used. Sheng Songcheng believes that to correctly understand the relationship between off-balance-sheet financing and on-balance-sheet financing, in line with regulatory requirements and risk prevention and control premise, appropriate retention of off-balance-sheet financing, increase the financing channels of enterprises, especially small and micro enterprises.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; text-indent: 28px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&quot;At the same time, we must&quot; open the front door &quot;. Lianping believes that we should grasp and control the rhythm and intensity of &quot;shadow financing&quot; such as rectifying trust loans and entrusted loans. In order to promote the steady growth of non-credit financing, we should also &quot;open the door&quot; to encourage and support those non-credit financing that can really meet the financing needs of the real economy, standardize reasonable trust loans and entrusted loans. Supplementary role of financing.</span></p>', '1534214434', '1535420936', '15');
INSERT INTO `sn_news` VALUES ('9', '/upload/news/20180814\\a1a5605fec2d9af53eff8ff9c5ae095a.png', '“穷病”怎么治，我来告诉你', 'I will tell you how to cure ', '<p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">日常总有朋友觉得自己的钱也不够花，看着身边有些人挣得还没自己多，可别人就能存下钱，这是为什么呢？很多人也会想着理财，但是又不知道如何理财，其实理财说难不难说简单也不简单，关键看你如何理财，不同的经济条件决定了不同的理财目标。</span></span></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; text-align: center;\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\"><img src=\"/ueditor/php/upload/image/20180814/1534215859266667.png\" title=\"1534215859266667.png\" alt=\"“穷病”怎么治，我来告诉你2.png\"/></span></span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><strong><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-weight:bold;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">积攒点钱以备不时之需</span></span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">明确目标，首先你要了解自己的花钱水平，如何花的钱，金钱观念是什么，然后树立一个自己想要达到的经济目标，但不可自大，树立的目标必须清楚明确具有真实性，这样才能让你做出正确的选择。</span></span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">了解收入及花销，很少有人清楚自己的钱是怎么花掉的，甚至不清楚自己到底有多少收入。没有这些基本信息，就很难制定预算，并以此合理安排钱财的使用，搞不清楚什么地方该花钱，也就不能在花费上作出合理的改变。想要达到自己的目标，就必须知道自己的钱都花到哪里去了，如何了解呢？那就是记录账目，看看自己的钱都花到哪里去了，只有明确自己金钱的去向，在能做出正确的改变。</span></span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">制定预算并实施，等到经济去向以及收入记录做好了，那么算出净资产就很容易了，这也是大多数理财专家计算财富的方式。只有清楚每年的净资产，才会掌握自己又朝目标前进了多少。很多人在刚开始时都抱怨拿不出更多的钱去投资，从而实现其经济目标。其实目标并不是依靠大笔的投入才能实现。削减开支，节省每一元钱，因为即使很小数目的投资，也可能会带来不小的财富。</span></span><strong><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-weight:bold;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\"><br/></span></span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; text-align: center;\"><img src=\"/ueditor/php/upload/image/20180814/1534216055416031.png\" title=\"1534216055416031.png\" alt=\"“穷病”怎么治，我来告诉你3.png\"/></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><strong><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-weight:bold;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">理财是让你的钱变的更值钱</span></span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">1. 如果是存银行的话可以存定期但是定期来说利息不高而且时间长，大家可以去银行购买30日或者50日理财产品，利息相对高，而且时间也不长；</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">2.此生第一笔投资千万别选择股票，股票风险极高、不要眼里只有收益，当你的投资心态还不够成熟以及知识储备不够是，你很容易把自己变成一个赌徒。在你没有足够的自制力和风险承受能力时，最好通过低风险来培养自己的能力。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">3.理财产品第三方机构也有很多，重要的是选择靠谱的单位加上合适的品种，才能使自己的钱更值钱，部分国内投资机构的理财师都是按照返点回扣来推荐理财产品的，他们的建议你只能作为参考。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">4.银行的理财产品，投资银行存款，余额宝，微信钱包等，收益跑不赢通胀，财富是不可能实现保值增值滴，只能让财产贬值速度放慢点。不要使用信用卡的分期付款和取现功能。不管没有利息，这样还会产生高昂的额外费用。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">5.风险相对高的，比如去银行购买债券或者基金，这些都是有专门机构操作，有风险但是一般行情还可以的时候收益比较高，也不用自己操作；另外一种投资理财的方式就是自己把握的方式，炒股，炒股就是高抛低吸的原则，每天最多可以盈利20%，同样亏也一样，选择行情还好的时候投资还是不错的，特别是对于闲钱来说；另外如果闲钱资金稍大，我们可以选择投资店铺开店或者投资项目，选择可靠稳定的项目，可以增加稳定的收入。</span></p><p><br/></p>', '<p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:Arial;font-size:14px\">Everyday there are always friends who feel that their money is not enough to spend, looking at some people around to earn more than themselves, but others can save money, why? Many people will also think about financial management, but do not know how to manage their finances, in fact, financial management is not difficult to say simple and not simple, the key is how you manage your finances, different economic conditions determine different financial goals.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; text-align: center;\"><img src=\"/ueditor/php/upload/image/20180814/1534216109119615.png\" title=\"1534216109119615.png\" alt=\"“穷病”怎么治，我来告诉你2.png\"/></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><strong><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-weight:bold;font-size:14px\">Save up some money for rainy days.</span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">Make sure you know your level of spending, how you spend your money, and what your concept of money is. Then set an economic goal you want to achieve, but don&#39;t be arrogant.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">Understanding income and spending, few people know how their money is spent, or even how much they earn. Without this basic information, it is difficult to make a budget and use it rationally. It is not clear where to spend money, and it is impossible to make reasonable changes in spending. If you want to achieve your goal, you must know where your money is going and how to understand it. That&#39;s to keep an account and see where your money is going. Only by knowing where your money is going can you make the right changes.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">Establishing a budget and implementing it, and when the economy and income records are in place, it&#39;s easy to calculate net worth, which is how most financial experts calculate wealth. Only by knowing the net assets per year can we grasp how much progress we have made towards the target. Many people complained at the beginning that they could not invest more money to achieve their economic goals. In fact, goals are not achieved through massive investment. Cut back and save every dollar, because even a small amount of investment can bring about a lot of wealth.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; text-align: center;\"><img src=\"/ueditor/php/upload/image/20180814/1534216145963696.png\" title=\"1534216145963696.png\" alt=\"“穷病”怎么治，我来告诉你3.png\"/></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><strong><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-weight:bold;font-size:14px\">Money management is to make your money more valuable.</span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">1. If it is a depositor&#39;s bank, you can deposit it regularly but the interest is not high and the time is long. People can go to the bank to buy 30 or 50 days of financial products, the interest is relatively high, and the time is not long.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">2. Don&#39;t choose stocks for the first time in your life. Stocks are extremely risky and don&#39;t only have returns. It&#39;s easy to turn yourself into a gambler when your investment mentality is not mature enough and you don&#39;t have enough knowledge. When you don&#39;t have enough self-control and risk tolerance, it&#39;s best to develop your ability through low risk.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">3. There are also many third-party financial products, it is important to choose reliable units plus the appropriate varieties, in order to make their own money more valuable, some domestic investment institutions are recommended financial products according to rebates, their recommendations can only be used as a reference.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">4. The bank&#39;s financial products, investment bank deposits, Bao yue, Weixin wallet, etc., the income does not beat inflation, wealth is impossible to maintain and increase the value of drops, only to slow down the pace of property depreciation. Do not use the installment and withdrawal functions of credit cards. Regardless of interest, there will be high additional costs.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; text-indent: 28px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">5. Relatively high risk, such as to the bank to buy bonds or funds, these are the operation of specialized agencies, risk but the general market can also be relatively high when the income, also do not have to operate their own; Another way of investment and financial management is their own grasp of the way, speculation, speculation is the principle of high-selling low-absorption, each. It can make a profit of up to 20% a day, but it is also a loss. It is good to invest when the market is good, especially for idle money. In addition, if the idle money is slightly larger, we can choose to invest in shops or investment projects, choose reliable and stable projects, which can increase stable income.</span></p>', '1534216148', '1535420917', '15');
INSERT INTO `sn_news` VALUES ('10', '/upload/news/20180814\\ac6a80393130f9a601e50f326f812894.jpg', '金融支持实体经济力度增强', 'Financial support for the strengthening of the real economy', '<p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">8月13日，中国人民银行发布7月金融统计数据显示，当月人民币贷款增加1.45万亿元，同比多增6278亿元，超出市场预期。7月末，广义货币（M2）增速也明显反弹，M2余额177.62万亿元，同比增长8.5%，增速比上月末高0.5个百分点。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">“新增贷款超预期主因是政策推动。央行加大资金投放，为银行提供流动性支持，同时，支持银行加大对小微企业、基础设施建设等特定领域投放。”交通银行金融研究中心首席金融分析师鄂永健认为，受新增贷款上升的带动，货币供应增速也有所回升。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">6月底以来，一系列增强银行服务实体经济能力的举措陆续落地。6月27日，央行印发《关于加大再贷款再贴现支持力度 引导金融机构增加小微企业信贷投放的通知》，增加支小支农再贷款和再贴现额度共1500亿元。同时，加大支小再贷款的政策优惠力度，下调支小再贷款利率0.5个百分点。7月5日起，央行定向降准0.5个百分点，释放了约7000亿元资金。鄂永健认为，总体而言，在政策推动下，融资增速有所回升，对实体经济支持力度增强。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">具体来看，</span>7月企业中长期贷款增加较多，当月增加4875亿元。鄂永健估计，这一部分以小企业和基础设施建设为主，说明政策推动效果明显，但当月票据融资较多，票据融资增加2388亿元，也说明7月融资需求还不是很强劲，后续随着相关政策陆续发力，预计会带动融资需求，未来融资增长或可期。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">另一引发广泛关注的是</span>M2增速反弹。7月末，M2增速环比回升0.5个百分点。中国民生银行首席研究员温彬认为，M2增速触底回升，反映当前市场流动性总体充裕，市场利率回落，银行信贷超预期增长，存款派生效应增强，市场流动性状况好转。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">值得注意的是，央行在</span>7月份对社会融资规模口径进行了调整，将“存款类金融机构资产支持证券”和“贷款核销”纳入社会融资规模统计，在“其他融资”项下反映。初步统计，新口径下，7月份社会融资规模增量为1.04万亿元，比上年同期少1242亿元。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">华泰证券宏观首席分析师李超认为，社会融资规模增速在信贷小幅放量的基础上没有出现反弹的主要原因是，表内信贷调整弹性和执行力度较强，而表外融资恢复则需要一定的时间。</span></span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; text-indent: 28px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">温彬也表示，</span>7月份社会融资规模增量为1.04万亿元，表明仍受委托贷款、信托等表外融资下降的拖累。7月20日，《关于进一步明确规范金融机构资产管理业务指导意见有关事项的通知》落地，明确了政策细节，增强了可操作性，增强了政策的确定性，给了市场一颗“定心丸”。随着资管新规和银行理财新规等落地，表外融资变动趋向平缓，将有利于社会融资规模增速保持平稳。</span></p>', '<p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">On August 13, the People&#39;s Bank of China released financial statistics for July, showing that Renminbi loans increased by 1.45 trillion yuan, an increase of 627.8 billion yuan, exceeding market expectations. At the end of July, the growth rate of the broad currency (M2) also rebounded markedly, with the balance of M2 amounting to 177.62 trillion yuan, up 8.5% year-on-year and 0.5 percentage points higher than at the end of last month.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&quot;The main reason for new loans exceeding expectations is policy driven. The central bank has increased its capital investment to provide liquidity support for banks, while supporting banks to increase investment in small and micro enterprises, infrastructure construction and other specific areas. Eyongjian, chief financial analyst at the Bank of Communications Financial Research Center, believes that money supply growth has also picked up, driven by the rise in new loans.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">Since the end of June, a series of initiatives to enhance the capacity of the banking sector to achieve real economy have come down. On June 27, the central bank issued the Circular on Enhancing Re-Discount Support for Renewal and Guiding Financial Institutions to Increase Credit Delivery for Small and Micro Enterprises (SMEs). The amount of re-loans and rediscounts for SMEs increased by 150 billion yuan. At the same time, we should increase the preferential policies for small loans and reduce the interest rate of small loans by 0.5 percentage points. Since July 5th, the central bank has lowered its target rate by 0.5 percentage points and released about 700 billion yuan of funds. Eyongjian believes that, in general, under the policy impetus, the financing growth rate has picked up, and the real economic support has strengthened.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">Specifically, in July, the number of medium and long-term loans increased considerably, and increased by 487 billion 500 million yuan in that month. E Yongjian estimates that this part is mainly for small enterprises and infrastructure construction, indicating that the policy has a significant effect on promoting, but more bill financing, bill financing increased by 238.8 billion yuan in July, also shows that the demand for financing is not very strong in July, follow-up with the relevant policies, is expected to drive financing demand, future financing growth. Or may be expected.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">Another widespread concern is the rebound in M2 growth. At the end of 7, M2 growth rate rebounded by 0.5 percentage points. Wen Bin, chief researcher at Minsheng Bank of China, believes that M2 growth has bottomed out and rebounded, reflecting the overall ample liquidity in the current market, the drop in market interest rates, the over-expected growth of bank credit, the strengthening of deposit distribution and the improvement of market liquidity.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">It is noteworthy that in July, the central bank adjusted the scale of social financing, including &quot;asset-backed securities of depository financial institutions&quot; and &quot;loan write-off&quot; into the statistics of social financing scale, which is reflected under &quot;other financing&quot;. Preliminary statistics show that under the new caliber, the increase of social financing scale in July was 1.04 trillion yuan, 124.2 billion yuan less than the same period last year.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">Li Chao, chief Macro Analyst of Huatai Securities, believes that the main reason why the growth rate of social financing did not rebound on the basis of a small reduction in credit is that the flexibility and execution of credit adjustment in the balance sheet is strong, while the recovery of off-balance sheet financing will take some time.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; text-indent: 28px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">Wen Bin also said that the increase in social financing scale in July was 1.04 trillion yuan, indicating that the decline of off-balance-sheet financing, such as entrusted loans and trusts, was still dragging on. On July 20, the Notice on Further Specification of Matters Relating to the Guiding Opinions on Asset Management of Financial Institutions landed, clarified the policy details, enhanced the operability, enhanced the policy certainty, and gave the market a &quot;reassurance pill&quot;. With the new regulations on capital management and banking and other new regulations landing, the changes of off-balance-sheet financing tend to be gentle, which will be conducive to maintaining a stable growth rate of social financing.</span></p>', '1534217332', '1535420898', '20');
INSERT INTO `sn_news` VALUES ('11', '/upload/news/20180814\\b02e802c6c95c5424b45e99590194c24.jpg', '人民银行试点开展金融债券弹性招标发行', 'The people\'s Bank of China launched a flexible tender for issuing financial bonds.', '<p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">8月13日，中国债券信息网发布了《中国人民银行金融市场司关于试点开展金融债券弹性招标发行的通知》。所谓弹性招标发行，是指金融机构在银行债券市场招标发行金融债券时，有权根据事先设定的规则，动态调整最终债券发行规模的行为。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">根据通知，试点阶段，单期金融债券发行规模弹性调整比例不得超过其初始发行规模的</span>50%。试点初期，弹性招标发行暂适用于开发性、政策性金融债券的发行，中国人民银行金融市场司可根据试点情况逐步扩大试点范围。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">通知还要求，金融债券招标触发发行规模弹性调整机制的，发行人应严格按照事先披露的规则进行调整操作。调整结果经发行人和中国人民银行观察员签字确认后方能生效，有关决策材料应妥善保存。</span></span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; text-indent: 28px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">在市场化发行方面，通知强调，金融债券发行应坚持市场化原则合理定价，充分体现金融债券的风险收益特征，不得以互持等方式扭曲金融债券定价。对于发行价格与二级市场上市交易价格偏离过大的情况，发行人或主承销商（如有）应在金融债券发行情况报告中予以说明，并有义务接受监管机构、市场机构的质询。</span></span></p>', '<p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">On August 13, the China Bond Information Network issued the Circular of the Financial Market Department of the People&#39;s Bank of China on the pilot implementation of flexible tender issuance of financial bonds. The so-called flexible tender issuance refers to the financial institutions in the bank bond market tender issuance of financial bonds, have the right to dynamically adjust the final bond issuance scale according to pre-set rules.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">According to the notice, in the pilot phase, the flexible adjustment ratio of the issuance scale of single-issue financial bonds shall not exceed 50% of their initial issuance scale. At the initial stage of the pilot project, flexible tender issuance is temporarily suitable for the issuance of developing and policy-oriented financial bonds. The Financial Market Department of the People&#39;s Bank of China may gradually expand the scope of the pilot project according to the pilot project.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">The notice also requires that the issuer should strictly follow the rules of prior disclosure to adjust the mechanism of flexible adjustment of issuance scale triggered by tendering of financial bonds. The result of the adjustment shall not come into effect until it is signed and confirmed by the issuer and the observer of the People&#39;s Bank of China, and the relevant decision-making materials shall be properly preserved.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; text-indent: 28px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">In the aspect of market-oriented issuance, the circular emphasizes that the issuance of financial bonds should adhere to the principle of market-oriented and reasonable pricing, fully embody the risk-return characteristics of financial bonds, and should not distort the pricing of financial bonds by means of interdependence. The issuer or the principal underwriter (if any) shall state in the financial bond issuance report that the issuance price deviates too much from the listed transaction price in the secondary market, and shall be obliged to accept the interrogation of the regulatory authorities and market institutions.</span></p>', '1534217962', '1535420890', '20');
INSERT INTO `sn_news` VALUES ('12', '/upload/news/20180814\\61cdd53d1528d7b89adf486d5e2884cd.jpg', '土耳其金融危机引发恐慌 欧元及澳元暴跌', 'Panic caused by Turkey\'s financial crisis and euro and Australian dollar slump', '<p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">上周五美国股市大幅受压，美国银行板块跌幅高达</span>2.5%，主要受到土耳其金融危机困扰。随着市场在波动性较高的情况下进入避险模式，美元受追捧走强。主要货币对大致下跌，欧元兑美元跌破1.15水平，澳元兑美元暴跌，穿0.73美元，二者均为最大受害者。由于上周市场波动及投资者对和对土耳其金融危机忧虑，亚太区投资者或迎来艰难的一天。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><strong><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-weight:bold;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">重磅数据满布整周，欧元及英镑受关注</span></span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">今周重磅数据一浪接一浪，第一浪由明天中期开始，包括中国工业生产产出，和零售数据。紧随其后为全球各国的通胀数据及各项经济指数。假如今周公布的欧盟</span>GPD和通胀数据暗示经济前景放缓加深市场忧虑，可能导致欧元波动加剧。英国方面，假如通胀数字和零售数据没有改善，或会令已经疲软的英镑进一步受压。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><strong><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-weight:bold;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">今日焦点</span></span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; text-indent: 28px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">债券市场反弹走高，与此相反商品价格面临下行压力。各项指标皆暗示投资者对潜在经济危机到担忧。投资者对各种新闻更加敏感，或会直接反映于市场走势上。亚太期货暗示交易开局或疲软。然而，美元走强以致本地货币走弱，可能会减轻投资者抛售的力度。</span></span></p>', '<p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">U.S. stocks fell sharply on Friday, with the U.S. banking sector falling as much as 2.5%, mainly due to the Turkish financial crisis. As the market entered a risk aversion under the condition of high volatility, the US dollar was highly sought after. Major currencies fell broadly, the euro fell below 1.15 against the dollar and the Australian dollar plunged below $0.73, both of which were the biggest victims. Investors in the Asia-Pacific region may have a tough day due to market volatility last week and concerns about the Turkish financial crisis.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><strong><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-weight:bold;font-size:14px\">The whole week is full of heavy data, and euro and pound are concerned.</span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">This week&#39;s heavy data has been pouring in, with the first wave starting in the middle of tomorrow, including China&#39;s industrial output and retail data. Followed by global inflation data and economic indicators. If the EU&#39;s GPD and inflation data released this week suggest a slowdown in the economic outlook deepens market concerns, it could lead to increased volatility in the euro. In the UK, if inflation and retail data do not improve, the already weak pound could be further weighed down.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><strong><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-weight:bold;font-size:14px\">Today&#39;s focus</span></strong></p><p><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">Bond market rebounded higher, and on the contrary, commodity prices are facing downward pressure. All indicators imply that investors are worried about potential economic crisis. Investors are more sensitive to news, or will be directly reflected in the market trend. Asia Pacific futures suggest trading starts or weakness. However, the weakening of the US dollar and weakening of local currencies may reduce the intensity of investors&#39; sell-off.</span></p>', '1534218785', '1535420883', '20');
INSERT INTO `sn_news` VALUES ('13', '/upload/news/20180814\\3683298db8459c0754c1e87c400fc98a.jpg', '科技金融热：炒作还是现实？看看这六大关键领域就知道了 ', 'Technology finance Craze: hype or reality? Look at these six key areas.', '<p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">事实再次证明我错了。</span></span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">八年来我一直预测科技金融投资将止步不前。而就</span>2018年年初的局面而言，情况并非如此。实际上，今年第一季度投入金融科技领域里的资金已经超过54亿美元，而且依然没有放缓的迹象。大家可以比较一下，2014年全年的金融科技投资还略低于40亿美元，也就是说四年时间里增长了五倍。研究机构Venture Scanner的数据显示，2001年的金融科技投资约为3亿美元。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">但所谓的</span>“金融科技”有点儿像个字谜。上个月我们和风投机构Nyca Partners共同举办了金融科技CEO峰会。就像我在会上告诉听众的那样，得到我们投资的那些CEO经营的实际上并不是“金融科技企业”，其中有支付公司，有贷款公司，也有人开发投资技术，或者向银行、保险公司或房地产开发商推销他们的产品。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">无论风投对有限合伙人说什么，也不管媒体怎样报道这个行业，这些公司之间未必有很大的瓜葛（除了显而易见的资本流动）。因此，尽管投资规模不断积累，但各个子行业之间的差异非常大。目前的实际情况值得我们更深入地进行探究。</span></span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><strong><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-weight:bold;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">支付：来过，做过</span></span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">10年前“金融科技”就等同于“支付”，原因是杰克·多尔西让硅谷的支付变得很酷。现在的情况已经截然不同。新建立的金融科技初创企业中几乎看不到支付公司的影子，近几年的初期融资额也在不断下滑。据我统计，2012年成立了大约90家支付公司，而2017年这个数字已经跌至10家以下。Billtrust和AvidXchange等商业支付公司仍有一定的受众（充分披露一下，我的团队对这些公司有投资），但如果跟踪趋势就会发现，今年或以后都不会出现大批支付类初创公司了。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">那么能量都跑到哪里了呢？答案是加密货币。和如今的加密货币公司创始人见面后，我可以把他们想象为几年前创立支付公司的那批人。二者有许多同样的基因，有类似的工程人才，其中一些的终端市场甚至都一样。</span></span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><strong><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-weight:bold;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">贷款：金融色彩盖过了科技</span></span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">贷款公司近来日子不好过，</span>2017年只获得了40亿美元投资，而且投资规模正在迅速下滑，特别是早期投资。贷款的交易和商品属性总是带来很大困难，现在投资界对这些初创公司的定义正在从科技公司变为贷款公司——Lending Club和OnDeck就是很明显的例子。GreenSky最近顺利首发上市，Funding Circle也蓄势待发，那就让我们看看它们能否改变投资者的想法。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><strong><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-weight:bold;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">财富</span>/投资：争相变成银行</span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">年复一年，财富科技公司在金融科技投资中一直稳定地占据一成份额。一种长期观点是它们代表着真正的颠覆机会。当下比较有意思的趋势之一是所有已经上了规模的财富和投资公司，比如</span>SoFi、Acorns和Wealthfront（再披露一下，我的团队一直在支持Acorns），都在做同一件事，那就是提供支票账户服务。大家可以一概而论，认为它们都想变成银行。不一定是有牌照的银行，而是打算通过第三方和新技术成为消费者的首要财务伙伴。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">这对我来说真的很耐人寻味，而且也给我们的行业和社会带来了一个重大问题，那就是消费者会放弃传统银行吗？他们会向自己的公司提交新的直存授权书，然后说</span>“把我的工资存到Betterment、Acorns或者SoFi那里”吗？这确实是个新现象。如果真是这样，金融科技就会迎来一个全新时代，那时候银行就会走出眼下的“帝国反击战”阶段，而且现在它们就会开始感到担心。这并不是说，如果不是这样财富科技就完蛋了，但所有这些公司同时出现同样的想法是一件引人关注的事。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><strong><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-weight:bold;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">保险：增长迅速推动全面发展</span></span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">保险初创公司目前确实是个焦点。</span>Oscar和众安保险等公司的融资规模在一年时间里从零增至数十亿美元，在此期间，它们决定全面发展。在历史上，Insureon和Zenefits两家保险初创企业只不过是经纪商或者对总代理人进行管理，但越来越多的人认为初创公司需要承保。我当然理解这样的冲动，因为如果不控制产品，资金就会被别人掌握。所以我明白这一点。但承保机构的权益回报率约为9%。风投没有理由向承保机构投资。一点儿也没有。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">今后，保险类科技公司需要把这件事想清楚。它将决定是保险真的发生转变，还是出现一大堆有着花哨</span>app的经纪商。另外，第二种情况并不会创造出很多权益价值。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><strong><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-weight:bold;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">房地产：全面颠覆</span></span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">房地产和加密货币是增长最多的两个领域。世界上最新出现的</span>10家独角兽公司中，有五家在房地产行业，它们是Compass、OpenDoor、WeWork、爱彼迎和UCommune，无论大家是否这么看这些公司。以OpenDoor为例，它发明了真正的“房地产”中介方法。这家公司并不是按售价的6%收取佣金，而是先把房地产买下来，然后找下家，通过买卖差价来赚钱。现在Zillow说他们也在这样做，其他一些公司也在迅速跟进。这个乏味的难以想象的行业，这个100年来都没有变化的行业正在经历重塑。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><strong><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-weight:bold;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">加密货币</span>/区块链：该认真起来了</span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">对加密货币我们能说什么呢？在去年的金融科技</span>CEO峰会上，我们说到了首次代币发行（ICO）会以怎样的方式把人送进监狱。虽然还没有人因此入狱，但这事很难说。ICO的规模仍在膨胀，今年3月曾达到41亿美元的高点，但一般来说每个月的规模约为15亿美元。此外，政府发出的声音越来越响，也越来越清晰，那就是这可不是什么避风港。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">除了</span>ICO，我们在研究加密货币领域时把它分成了三部分，分别是加密货币投资生态系统、企业区块链和分布式应用。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">对于第一部分，关键问题在于加密货币会成为一种资产吗？我暂时认为答案是肯定的。这个投资生态系统目前正在顺利成熟，</span>Basis和Compound等几家走在前面的公司（最后披露一下，这两家都是我们投资的公司）正在打造市场结构的关键组成部分，其假设前提是今后人们会希望更多地进行大规模加密货币交易。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">就企业区块链而言，它真的是一个独立行当吗？基于新闻报道判断，这个市场正在蓬勃发展，但如果在验证概念之余还要获得收入，这个市场就算不上繁荣。在初期阶段，我们暂时对这个问题说</span>“不”，但出色的创业者们正在为此付出努力，而且我确信他们将证明我们是错的。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">最后，分布式应用堪称一项大奖。它显然才刚刚起步，但人才正在向这里聚集。未来的爱彼迎、</span>Uber和Amazon Web Services真的会变成由代币驱动的开源协议，进而改变我们存储文件、预定房间、订票和管理行程的方式吗？我不知道这种局面什么时候到来，但我相信它会到来。总有这么一天。</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><strong><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-weight:bold;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">红利趋势：新老势力合二为一？</span></span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">刚刚进入金融科技领域时，这个行业的主要参与者是把产品卖给银行的供应商。在我们这些开始投资的人中，许多人都把自己摆在对立面，他们说不，金融科技创业者能比现有公司做的更好。现在，大银行越来越想了解那些它们应该纳入采购范围的新供应商，这样就可以跟后者合作并采用它们的技术，从而让自己变得更像现代企业。</span></span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">这些银行如今也开始收购上述</span>“挑战者”。去年我还不会做出这样的预测，而摩根大通、高盛、Capital One和西班牙对外银行目前都在这样做。这些银行认为收购金融科技公司并非禁忌。对所有跟我们合作的人来说，这都是一个重大而积极的变化。就让我们看看它能持续多长时间吧。（财富中文网）</span></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; text-indent: 28px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\";font-family:微软雅黑;font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:微软雅黑\">马特</span>·哈里斯是贝恩风投董事总经理。他一直是科技金融方面的顶尖投资人之一，从2000年起一直在这个领域活动。 </span></p>', '<p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">I<span style=\"font-family:宋体\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">ve been proven wrong once again.</span></span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">For eight years running, I<span style=\"font-family:宋体\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">ve predicted that fintech investment is going to plateau. Based on the start of 2018, it hasn</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">t yet. In fact, we saw more than $5.4 billion invested in fintech during the first quarter of the year, with no signs of slowing momentum. For perspective, fintech investment for all of 2014 was just under $4 billion, so that</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">s </span><span style=\"font-family:宋体\">“</span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">5x</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体\">” </span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">growth in four years. In 2001, per data from Venture Scanner, it was something like $300 million.</span></span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">With that said, this whole <span style=\"font-family:宋体\">“</span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">fintech</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体\">” </span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">thing is kind of a charade. As I shared with attendees last month during our annual Fintech CEO Summit, co-hosted together with Nyca Partners, the CEOs in our portfolios don</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">t actually run </span><span style=\"font-family:宋体\">“</span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">fintech businesses.</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体\">” </span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">They run a payments business or a lending business, or they build investing technologies, or they sell to banks or insurance or real estate companies.</span></span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">Regardless of what VCs tell limited partners, or how media cover the industry, these businesses don<span style=\"font-family:宋体\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">t necessarily have much to do with each other (besides the obvious of moving money around). So while the investment numbers are up in aggregate, each sub-sector has a very different story. And it</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">s worth diving in more deeply to understand what</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">s really going on.</span></span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><strong><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-weight:bold;font-size:14px\">Payments: Been there, done that</span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">Ten years ago, <span style=\"font-family:宋体\">“</span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">fintech</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体\">” </span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">equaled </span><span style=\"font-family:宋体\">“</span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">payments</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体\">” </span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">because Jack Dorsey made payments cool in Silicon Valley. That</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">s very different now. Payments is a distinct minority of new fintech startups, and early-stage funding has dipped over the past few years. In 2012, about 90 payment companies were founded by my count. In 2017, that number dropped down below 10. Commercial payment companies like Billtrust and AvidXchange are still having a bit of a moment (full disclosure: my team has invested in these firms), but if you follow the trends, you won</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">t see tons of payment startups this year or going forward.</span></span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">Where did the energy go? Cryptocurrency. When I meet with cryptocurrency founders today, I can imagine those folks a few years ago being payments founders. It<span style=\"font-family:宋体\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">s a lot of the same DNA, similar engineering talent, and even some of the same end markets.</span></span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><strong><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-weight:bold;font-size:14px\">Lending: More fin than tech</span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">The lending sector is a tough business these days, with investment of just $4 billion in 2017 and dropping fast, especially in early stages. The transactional and commodity natures of lending always made it hard, and now the investment community re-rated those startups from technology companies to lending companies<span style=\"font-family:宋体\">—</span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">Lending Club and OnDeck being the obvious examples. With GreenSky recently having a successful public debut and Funding Circle waiting in the wings, we</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">ll see if they can change investors</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体\">’ </span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">minds.</span></span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><strong><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-weight:bold;font-size:14px\">Wealth/Investing: Race to the bank</span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">Wealth tech companies get a steady 10% of fintech investment year after year. There<span style=\"font-family:宋体\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">s a durable view that they show real opportunity for disruption. One of the more interesting trends right now is that all the wealth and investment companies that have achieved scale</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体\">—</span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">like SoFi, Acorns, and Wealthfront (another disclosure: my team has backed Acorns)</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体\">—</span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">are doing the same thing: They</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">re adding a checking account. You could paint with a broad brush and say they are all trying to become banks. Not necessarily licensed banks, but rather, leveraging third parties and new technologies to try to become a consumer</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">s primary financial partner.</span></span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">This is really fascinating to me and raises a key question for our industry, and our society: Will consumers bail on traditional banks? Will they go to their employer with a new direct deposit authorization form and say <span style=\"font-family:宋体\">“</span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">send my money to Betterment, to Acorns, to SoFi</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体\">”</span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">? This is truly a new phenomenon. If it works, there</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">s a whole new era of fintech coming, where the banks go from the </span><span style=\"font-family:宋体\">“</span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">Empire Strikes Back</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体\">” </span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">phase that they</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">re in right now</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体\">—</span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">and they start to worry again. It doesn</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">t mean wealth tech is toast if it doesn</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">t work, but it</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">s striking that all these companies had the same ideas at the same time.</span></span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><strong><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-weight:bold;font-size:14px\">Insurance: Fast growth leads to full stack</span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">Insurance startups are really at a pivot right now. Companies like Oscar or ZhongAn have scaled from nothing to billions a year in funding, and in the process, they<span style=\"font-family:宋体\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">ve decided to be full stack. Historically, insurance startups Insureon and Zenefits were simply brokers or managing general agents, but increasingly there</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">s a take that startups need to be(come) carriers. I certainly understand that instinct</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体\">—</span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">if you don</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">t control the product, someone else controls the capital. So, I get it. But return on equity for carriers tends to be around 9%. It doesn</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">t make sense for a VC to invest in a carrier. Not at all.</span></span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">Moving forward, the insurance tech players need to figure this out. It will be the difference between insurance getting really transformed or having a bunch of brokers with fancy apps. And that second future is not going to create a lot of equity value.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><strong><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-weight:bold;font-size:14px\">Real Estate: Disruption in full effect</span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">Real estate and crypto are the two areas where we see the most growth. In real estate, five of the venture world<span style=\"font-family:宋体\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">s 10 most recent unicorns</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体\">—</span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">Compass, OpenDoor, WeWork, Airbnb and UCommune</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体\">—</span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">are real estate companies, whether you think of them that way or not. OpenDoor, for instance, invented a true </span><span style=\"font-family:宋体\">“</span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">prop</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体\">” </span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">brokerage, where they don</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">t broker a sale for 6%, but instead buy the property, find another buyer and make money on the spread. Zillow now says they</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">re doing the same thing, and there have been a bunch of fast followers. This incredibly stodgy industry</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体\">—</span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">which hasn</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">t changed in a hundred years</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体\">—</span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">is getting re-made.</span></span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><strong><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-weight:bold;font-size:14px\">Cryptocurrency/Blockchain: Time to get serious</span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">What can we say about crypto? Last year at our Fintech CEO Summit, we talked about how people were going to go to jail for initial coin offerings (ICOs). No one has gone to jail yet, but it<span style=\"font-family:宋体\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">s tricky. ICO volume is still frothy, with a peak of $4.1 billion raised in March but otherwise running at roughly $1.5 billion a month. Plus, the noise out of government is getting louder and clearer that this is not some sort of safe harbor.</span></span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">Beyond ICOs, we think about the crypto space in three parts: the crypto investing ecosystem, enterprise blockchain, and distributed applications.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">For the first, a key question is: Will crypto be an asset class? Provisionally, I believe the answer is <span style=\"font-family:宋体\">“</span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">yes.</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体\">” </span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">The investing ecosystem is now maturing nicely, and several pioneers like Basis and Compound (last disclosure: both are portfolio companies), are filling in key elements of market structure, assuming people want to trade crypto at scale more in the future.</span></span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">Regarding enterprise blockchain, is it actually a standalone business? The market is thriving if you count press releases, but not if you look for revenueoutside of proof-of-concept. We provisionally said <span style=\"font-family:宋体\">“</span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">no</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体\">” </span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">to this question in the early days, but we have great entrepreneurs working on it</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体\">—</span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">and I</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">m sure they</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">ll prove us wrong.</span></span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">Finally, distributed applications are the big prize. It<span style=\"font-family:宋体\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">s clearly early days, but this is where the talent is heading. Will the Airbnb, Uber, and Amazon Web Services of the future simply be open source protocols powered by tokens that change the way we store our files, book our houses, book our travel, and manage our transportation? I don</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">t know when, but I believe we</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">ll get there. Someday.</span></span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><strong><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-weight:bold;font-size:14px\">Bonus trend: Incumbents and insurgents unite?</span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">When I started in fintech, the industry was primarily made up of vendors that sold to banks. Many of us who started investing set ourselves in opposition to that and said, No, fintech can be entrepreneurs who do a better job than the incumbents. Now, the big banks increasingly want to know about new vendors they should push through procurement, so they can partner and deploy their technology to become more like modern companies.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right:0;margin-left:0;text-indent:28px;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">Those banks are also now acquiring the insurgents. I would not have predicted this last year, but JPMorgan Chase, Goldman Sachs, Capital One, and BBVA have processes that are under way right now. The banks have decided it is not taboo to buy fintech companies. That<span style=\"font-family:宋体\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">s a meaningful and positive change for everyone with whom we work. We</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">ll see how lasting it is.</span></span></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; text-indent: 28px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\";font-family:宋体;font-size:14px\">Matt Harris is a managing director at Bain Capital Ventures. He is consistently ranked as one of the top investors in fintech, having participated in the space since 2000. </span></p>', '1534219364', '1535420741', '20');
